.TH smi-create-venv "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Python Command"
.SH NAME
smi-create-venv \- Create and initialize a Python virtual environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-create-venv
.RI [ PYTHON_PACKAGE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-create-venv
creates a new Python virtual environment in the current directory under \fB./.venv\fR.
.PP
If a \fIPYTHON_PACKAGE\fR name is provided (e.g., \fBpython311\fR), the script:
.IP 1.
Includes the corresponding SMI package definition to determine the \fBPYTHON_VERSION\fR.
.IP 2.
Sets \fBPYTHON_HOME\fR to \fB/opt/python-${PYTHON_VERSION}\fR.
.IP 3.
Updates the \fBPATH\fR to use the binary directory of that Python version.
.PP
The initialization process involves:
.IP 1.
Running \fBpython3 -m venv ./.venv\fR.
.IP 2.
Activating the environment.
.IP 3.
Upgrading \fBpip\fR to the latest version.
